<snippet>
	<content><![CDATA[const decapitalize = ([first, ...rest], upperRest = false) =>
  first.toLowerCase() + (upperRest ? rest.join('').toUpperCase() : rest.join(''));]]></content>
	<description>Decapitalizes the first letter of a string.  Use array destructuring and `String.toLowerCase()` to decapitalize first letter, `...rest` to get array of characters after first letter and then `Array.join('')` to make it a string again. Omit the `upperRest` parameter to keep the rest of the string intact, or set it to `true` to convert to uppercase.</description>
